Enums.name: ChatRole

values.name: system
values.description: The role that instructs or sets the behavior of the assistant.

values.name: user
values.description: The role that provides input for chat completions.

values.name: assistant
values.description: The role that provides responses to system-instructed, user-prompted input.

values.name: tool
values.description: The role that represents extension tool activity within a chat completions operation.

Enums.description: A description of the intended purpose of a message within a chat completions interaction.

Enums.name: ChatMessageImageDetailLevel

values.name: auto
values.description: Specifies that the model should determine which detail level to apply using heuristics like image size.

values.name: low
values.description:
Specifies that image evaluation should be constrained to the 'low-res' model that may be faster and consume fewer
tokens but may also be less accurate for highly detailed images.

values.name: high
values.description:
Specifies that image evaluation should enable the 'high-res' model that may be more accurate for highly detailed
images but may also be slower and consume more tokens.

Enums.description: A representation of the possible image detail levels for image-based chat completions message content.

Enums.name: ChatCompletionsToolSelectionPreset

values.name: auto
values.description:
Specifies that the model may either use any of the tools provided in this chat completions request or
instead return a standard chat completions response as if no tools were provided.

values.name: none
values.description:
Specifies that the model should not respond with a tool call and should instead provide a standard chat
completions response. Response content may still be influenced by the provided tool definitions.

values.name: required
values.description: Specifies that the model should respond with a call to one or more tools.

Enums.description: Represents a generic policy for how a chat completions tool may be selected.

Enums.name: ExtraParameters

values.name: error
values.description: The service will error if it detected extra parameters in the request payload. This is the service default.

values.name: drop
values.description: The service will ignore (drop) extra parameters in the request payload. It will only pass the known parameters to the back-end AI model.

values.name: pass_through
values.description: The service will pass extra parameters to the back-end AI model.

Enums.description: Controls what happens if extra parameters, undefined by the REST API, are passed in the JSON request payload.

Enums.name: CompletionsFinishReason

values.name: stopped
values.description: Completions ended normally and reached its end of token generation.

values.name: tokenLimitReached
values.description: Completions exhausted available token limits before generation could complete.

values.name: contentFiltered
values.description:
Completions generated a response that was identified as potentially sensitive per content
moderation policies.

values.name: toolCalls
values.description: Completion ended with the model calling a provided tool for output.

Enums.description: Representation of the manner in which a completions response concluded.

Models.name: ChatCompletionsOptions
Models.description:
The configuration information for a chat completions request.
Completions support a wide variety of tasks and generate text that continues from or "completes"
provided prompt data.

properties.name: messages
properties.description:
The collection of context messages associated with this chat completions request.
Typical usage begins with a chat message for the System role that provides instructions for
the behavior of the assistant, followed by alternating messages between the User and
Assistant roles.

valueType.name: ChatRequestMessage
valueType.description: An abstract representation of a chat message as provided in a request.

discriminatorProperty.name: role
discriminatorProperty.description: The chat role associated with this message.

system.name: ChatRequestSystemMessage
system.description:
A request chat message containing system instructions that influence how the model will generate a chat completions
response.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The chat role associated with this message, which is always 'system' for system messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the system message.

user.name: ChatRequestUserMessage
user.description: A request chat message representing user input to the assistant.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The chat role associated with this message, which is always 'user' for user messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The contents of the user message, with available input types varying by selected model.

valueType.name: ChatMessageContentItem
valueType.description: An abstract representation of a structured content item within a chat message.

text.name: ChatMessageTextContentItem
text.description: A structured chat content item containing plain text.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The discriminated object type: always 'text' for this type.

properties.name: text
properties.description: The content of the message.

image_url.name: ChatMessageImageContentItem
image_url.description: A structured chat content item containing an image reference.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The discriminated object type: always 'image_url' for this type.

properties.name: imageUrl
properties.description: An internet location, which must be accessible to the model,from which the image may be retrieved.

type.name: ChatMessageImageUrl
type.description: An internet location from which the model may retrieve an image.

properties.name: url
properties.description: The URL of the image.

properties.name: detail
properties.description:
The evaluation quality setting to use, which controls relative prioritization of speed, token consumption, and
accuracy.

assistant.name: ChatRequestAssistantMessage
assistant.description: A request chat message representing response or action from the assistant.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The chat role associated with this message, which is always 'assistant' for assistant messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The content of the message.

properties.name: toolCalls
properties.description:
The tool calls that must be resolved and have their outputs appended to subsequent input messages for the chat
completions request to resolve as configured.

valueType.name: ChatCompletionsToolCall
valueType.description:
An abstract representation of a tool call that must be resolved in a subsequent request to perform the requested
chat completion.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The ID of the tool call.

function.name: ChatCompletionsFunctionToolCall
function.description:
A tool call to a function tool, issued by the model in evaluation of a configured function tool, that represents
a function invocation needed for a subsequent chat completions request to resolve.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of tool call, in this case always 'function'.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The details of the function invocation requested by the tool call.

type.name: FunctionCall
type.description: The name and arguments of a function that should be called, as generated by the model.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to call.

properties.name: arguments
properties.description:
The arguments to call the function with, as generated by the model in JSON format.
Note that the model does not always generate valid JSON, and may hallucinate parameters
not defined by your function schema. Validate the arguments in your code before calling
your function.

tool.name: ChatRequestToolMessage
tool.description: A request chat message representing requested output from a configured tool.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The chat role associated with this message, which is always 'tool' for tool messages.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The content of the message.

properties.name: toolCallId
properties.description: The ID of the tool call resolved by the provided content.

properties.name: frequency_penalty
properties.description:
A value that influences the probability of generated tokens appearing based on their cumulative
frequency in generated text.
Positive values will make tokens less likely to appear as their frequency increases and
decrease the likelihood of the model repeating the same statements verbatim.
Supported range is [-2, 2].

properties.name: InternalShouldStreamResponse
properties.description: A value indicating whether chat completions should be streamed for this request.

properties.name: presence_penalty
properties.description:
A value that influences the probability of generated tokens appearing based on their existing
presence in generated text.
Positive values will make tokens less likely to appear when they already exist and increase the
model's likelihood to output new topics.
Supported range is [-2, 2].

properties.name: temperature
properties.description:
The sampling temperature to use that controls the apparent creativity of generated completions.
Higher values will make output more random while lower values will make results more focused
and deterministic.
It is not recommended to modify temperature and top_p for the same completions request as the
interaction of these two settings is difficult to predict.
Supported range is [0, 1].

properties.name: NucleusSamplingFactor
properties.description:
An alternative to sampling with temperature called nucleus sampling. This value causes the
model to consider the results of tokens with the provided probability mass. As an example, a
value of 0.15 will cause only the tokens comprising the top 15% of probability mass to be
considered.
It is not recommended to modify temperature and top_p for the same completions request as the
interaction of these two settings is difficult to predict.
Supported range is [0, 1].

properties.name: max_tokens
properties.description: The maximum number of tokens to generate.

properties.name: response_format
properties.description:
The format that the model must output. Use this to enable JSON mode instead of the default text mode.
Note that to enable JSON mode, some AI models may also require you to instruct the model to produce JSON
via a system or user message.

type.name: ChatCompletionsResponseFormat
type.description:
Represents the format that the model must output. Use this to enable JSON mode instead of the default text mode.
Note that to enable JSON mode, some AI models may also require you to instruct the model to produce JSON
via a system or user message.

discriminatorProperty.name: type
discriminatorProperty.description: The response format type to use for chat completions.

text.name: ChatCompletionsResponseFormatText
text.description: A response format for Chat Completions that emits text responses. This is the default response format.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Response format type: always 'text' for this object.

json_object.name: ChatCompletionsResponseFormatJSON
json_object.description:
A response format for Chat Completions that restricts responses to emitting valid JSON objects.
Note that to enable JSON mode, some AI models may also require you to instruct the model to produce JSON
via a system or user message.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Response format type: always 'json_object' for this object.

properties.name: StopSequences
properties.description: A collection of textual sequences that will end completions generation.

properties.name: tools
properties.description: The available tool definitions that the chat completions request can use, including caller-defined functions.

valueType.name: ChatCompletionsToolDefinition
valueType.description: An abstract representation of a tool that can be used by the model to improve a chat completions response.

function.name: ChatCompletionsFunctionToolDefinition
function.description: The definition information for a chat completions function tool that can call a function in response to a tool call.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The object name, which is always 'function'.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The function definition details for the function tool.

type.name: FunctionDefinition
type.description: The definition of a caller-specified function that chat completions may invoke in response to matching user input.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function to be called.

properties.name: description
properties.description:
A description of what the function does. The model will use this description when selecting the function and
interpreting its parameters.

properties.name: parameters
properties.description: The parameters the function accepts, described as a JSON Schema object.

properties.name: toolChoice
properties.description: If specified, the model will configure which of the provided tools it can use for the chat completions response.

variantTypes.name: ChatCompletionsNamedToolSelection
variantTypes.description: An abstract representation of an explicit, named tool selection to use for a chat completions request.

function.name: ChatCompletionsNamedFunctionToolSelection
function.description: A tool selection of a specific, named function tool that will limit chat completions to using the named function.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The object type, which is always 'function'.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The function that should be called.

type.name: ChatCompletionsFunctionToolSelection
type.description: A tool selection of a specific, named function tool that will limit chat completions to using the named function.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the function that should be called.

properties.name: seed
properties.description:
If specified, the system will make a best effort to sample deterministically such that repeated requests with the
same seed and parameters should return the same result. Determinism is not guaranteed.

properties.name: model
properties.description: ID of the specific AI model to use, if more than one model is available on the endpoint.

Models.name: ChatCompletions
Models.description:
Representation of the response data from a chat completions request.
Completions support a wide variety of tasks and generate text that continues from or "completes"
provided prompt data.

properties.name: id
properties.description: A unique identifier associated with this chat completions response.

properties.name: created
properties.description:
The first timestamp associated with generation activity for this completions response,
represented as seconds since the beginning of the Unix epoch of 00:00 on 1 Jan 1970.

properties.name: model
properties.description: The model used for the chat completion.

properties.name: usage
properties.description: Usage information for tokens processed and generated as part of this completions operation.

type.name: CompletionsUsage
type.description:
Representation of the token counts processed for a completions request.
Counts consider all tokens across prompts, choices, choice alternates, best_of generations, and
other consumers.

properties.name: completion_tokens
properties.description: The number of tokens generated across all completions emissions.

properties.name: prompt_tokens
properties.description: The number of tokens in the provided prompts for the completions request.

properties.name: total_tokens
properties.description: The total number of tokens processed for the completions request and response.

properties.name: choices
properties.description:
The collection of completions choices associated with this completions response.
Generally, `n` choices are generated per provided prompt with a default value of 1.
Token limits and other settings may limit the number of choices generated.

valueType.name: ChatChoice
valueType.description:
The representation of a single prompt completion as part of an overall chat completions request.
Generally, `n` choices are generated per provided prompt with a default value of 1.
Token limits and other settings may limit the number of choices generated.

properties.name: index
properties.description: The ordered index associated with this chat completions choice.

properties.name: finish_reason
properties.description: The reason that this chat completions choice completed its generated.

properties.name: message
properties.description: The chat message for a given chat completions prompt.

type.name: ChatResponseMessage
type.description: A representation of a chat message as received in a response.

properties.name: role
properties.description: The chat role associated with the message.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The content of the message.

properties.name: toolCalls
properties.description:
The tool calls that must be resolved and have their outputs appended to subsequent input messages for the chat
completions request to resolve as configured.

Models.name: ModelInfo
Models.description: Represents some basic information about the AI model.

properties.name: model_name
properties.description: The name of the AI model. For example: `Phi21`

properties.name: model_type
properties.description: The type of the AI model. A Unique identifier for the profile.

properties.name: model_provider_name
properties.description: The model provider name. For example: `Microsoft Research`

Models.name: StreamingChatCompletionsUpdate
Models.description:
Represents a response update to a chat completions request, when the service is streaming updates 
using Server Sent Events (SSE).
Completions support a wide variety of tasks and generate text that continues from or "completes"
provided prompt data.

properties.name: id
properties.description: A unique identifier associated with this chat completions response.

properties.name: created
properties.description:
The first timestamp associated with generation activity for this completions response,
represented as seconds since the beginning of the Unix epoch of 00:00 on 1 Jan 1970.

properties.name: model
properties.description: The model used for the chat completion.

properties.name: usage
properties.description: Usage information for tokens processed and generated as part of this completions operation.

properties.name: choices
properties.description:
An update to the collection of completion choices associated with this completions response.
Generally, `n` choices are generated per provided prompt with a default value of 1.
Token limits and other settings may limit the number of choices generated.

valueType.name: StreamingChatChoiceUpdate
valueType.description:
Represents an update to a single prompt completion when the service is streaming updates 
using Server Sent Events (SSE).
Generally, `n` choices are generated per provided prompt with a default value of 1.
Token limits and other settings may limit the number of choices generated.

properties.name: index
properties.description: The ordered index associated with this chat completions choice.

properties.name: finish_reason
properties.description: The reason that this chat completions choice completed its generated.

properties.name: delta
properties.description: An update to the chat message for a given chat completions prompt.

Operations.Name: complete
Operations.Description:
Gets chat completions for the provided chat messages.
Completions support a wide variety of tasks and generate text that continues from or "completes"
provided prompt data. The method makes a REST API call to the `/chat/completions` route
on the given endpoint.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: contentType
Parameters.Description: Body parameter's content type. Known values are application/json

Operations.Name: getModelInfo
Operations.Description:
Returns information about the AI model.
The method makes a REST API call to the `/info` route on the given endpoint.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.
